President Biden and Prime Minister Narendra Modi of India met in Tokyo to reaffirm their commitment to working together for a prosperous and secure world. They discussed deepening their defense partnership, promoting economic engagement, and expanding cooperation on global health and emerging technologies. Climate change was also a key topic, with a focus on accelerating India's energy transition. President Biden condemned Russia's war against Ukraine and both leaders pledged to provide humanitarian assistance and manage disruptions caused by the conflict. They also emphasized the importance of their democratic values and expressed pride in the achievements of the Quad partnership.